lowing for unconventional observations to be made. Furthermore, the volume offers means for the cultural contextualization of Wittgenstein's thoughts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 4aCarroll, Lewis. 4aGoethe, Johann Wolfgang von. 4aLiteratur. 4aLiterature. 4aPhilosophie. 4aPhilosophy. 4aShakespeare, William. 4aWittgenstein, Ludwig. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Modern.2bisacsh1 aBru, Sascha, eeditor.1 aHuemer, Wolfgang, eeditor.1 aSteuer, Daniel, eeditor.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949oZDB-23-GPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2013z978311031732908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE  2013z9783110317312oZDB-23-DPH0 cprintz978311029462040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110294699423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110294699.jpg  a978-3-11-023848-8  DGBA Backlist Philosophy English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  a978-3-11-031732-9  E-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2013b2013  aDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014c2000d2014  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGGb2013